VESICULAR STOMATITIS, HORSES - USA (COLORADO) (02)
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Vesicular stomatitis, horses - USA (Colorado) 980730002322
Date: Wed, 29 Jul 1998 16:54:56 -0500
Source: USDA Weekly Update <http://www.aphis.usda.gov/vs/ep/>
Via: Martin Hugh-Jones <mehj2020@vt8200.vetmed.lsu.edu>

[Here is the full script from the latest USDA/APHIS/VS Vesicular Stomatitis
Weekly Update, Number 10, for 24 July, 1998. - MHJ

Colorado became a case positive state on July 23, 1998, with the isolation
of VSV, Indiana strain, from a horse on premises located in Boulder County.
Nine additional investigations were reported, six of which were positive
for VSV. There were two positive premises in Boulder County and four
positive premises in Weld County. One of the positive premises in Weld
County was also positive for virus isolation. Two investigations are
pending, and one is negative. There are a total of seven positive VSV
premises in Colorado.
No new VSV investigations were reported in Arizona, where the total number
of positive premises remains at fifteen.
Two new VSV investigations were reported in New Mexico, one of which was
positive for VSV. The new positive premises are located in Sandoval County.
The other investigation is still pending. The new positive premises bring
the total in New Mexico to nine.
No new investigations were reported in Texas, where the number of positive
premises remains at one.
This update reflects only the investigations in case positive states after
the index case was reported.
All positive cases in the four affected States have been of the equine
species.
--
